Subject: Re: [T2] VDO oil temp sender drain plug, Redux

>Has anyone
>successfully installed a VDO 323055 drain plug oil sender in a 1600 upright
>engine fitted with a stock oil screen, and if so, how in the blast did you
>manage it?

I drilled an offset hole in the sump plate.  IIRC for the one I had, the instructions had a diagram of where to do this? and also a thin nut to anchor the sender on the inside.  I sealed the install with JBWeld.

